{"id":"MU-001","date":"2026-07-19","author":"duke@worldtree.io","target":"verdict","change":"suppress","trigger_observation":"First end-to-end port run (logs+quantities, 2026-07-18) waived 8/8 structural punch items as one conscious paradigm divergence (PHP plugin registry -> local-first event log). A 100%-waivable structural gate provided no independent acceptance evidence; from the outside it was indistinguishable from a disabled gate.","replacement_signal":"Acceptance moves to the value-equivalence oracle (semantic fixture pack, 7/7 that run). Structural discipline is carried by the pre-registered paradigm-divergence declaration; structural FAILURE is redefined as unpredictedWaiverCount>0 OR staleWaiverCount>0 OR a binding-gate (fidelity) failure. The verdict is downgraded to advisory ONLY when consistency_model or coordination_layer diverge; matching paradigms keep binding gating unchanged.","reversal_condition":"Restore binding verdict for a paradigm class if a future run shows structural gates carry independent acceptance signal there — i.e. a value-equivalent port is rejected by a structural gate (false-negative on the oracle caught by structure), or unpredicted-waiver rate stays 0 across >=3 ports while gates still fail, proving the gates track real divergence the oracle misses.","evidence_refs":["eval/ctkr/results/vertical-slice-logs-quantities.md#stage-3-verify","docs/design/meta-structural-pass.md"],"supersedes":null}
{"id":"MU-002","date":"2026-07-19","author":"duke@worldtree.io","target":"prediction-model","change":"add","trigger_observation":"Under the 2026-07-18 central-authority->local-first divergence, all 8 punch items landed on role-coverage/interface-preservation/composition-preservation/cycle-consistency and were waived; fidelity alone hit ceiling (100%), the only real structural signal.","replacement_signal":"predictNonInformativeGates() pre-registers those four gates as non-informative and keeps fidelity binding, so post-run waivers on them are expected (predicted) and a waiver on fidelity is an unpredicted-waiver signal.","reversal_condition":"Revise the predicted set if a second cross-paradigm port shows a currently-predicted gate carrying real signal (e.g. composition preservation holding for a value-flow operad), or shows fidelity being legitimately waivable under divergence.","evidence_refs":["eval/ctkr/results/vertical-slice-logs-quantities.md#stage-3b","docs/design/meta-structural-pass.md#a"],"supersedes":null}
